title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\ResourceCommitment
name: ResourceCommitment
description:
Commitment for a particular resource (a Commitment is composed of one or more of these).

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.ResourceCommitment

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.accelerator_type
params.description: Name of the accelerator type resource. Applicable only when the type is ACCELERATOR.

params.name: data.amount
params.description: The amount of the resource purchased (in a type-dependent unit, such as bytes). For vCPUs, this can just be an integer. For memory, this must be provided in MB. Memory must be a multiple of 256 MB, with up to 6.5GB of memory per every vCPU.

params.name: data.type
params.description: Type of resource for which this commitment applies. Possible values are VCPU and MEMORY Check the Type enum for the list of possible values.
